history.content:
Depends on if "last year" refers to last semester or not.

If this was before: then you are free to retake classes you failed, and the grade will count towards whatever you want.

If this was last semester: then the grade will still count towards whatever you want, but for purposes of calculating your CS declaration GPA, your NP would also be counted, as per @3105. For CogSci or any other purposes, nothing changes.

I ended up no passing cs61a last year and I want to retake it for a letter grade. Assuming that I get a sufficient letter grade in the class, does it count towards either an intended cs or cogsci major in terms of prereqs? Or because I retook it will I not be able to major in cs or cogsci anymore?
